Sentencas: The effects of doping a trace of Fe2O3 on the structural and electrical properties of 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia (8YSZ) are investigated.
Titulo: Effects of Fe2O3 doping on structural and electrical properties of 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The 8YSZ electrolytes doped with various Fe2O3 contents are applied to a solid oxide fuel cell to confirm whether it is positive or negative for SOFC performances.
Titulo: Effects of Fe2O3 doping on structural and electrical properties of 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, the 8YSZ electrolyte with a trace of Fe2O3 shows the increased oxygen vacancies and better ionic conductivity.
Titulo: Effects of Fe2O3 doping on structural and electrical properties of 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The optimum Fe2O3 doping content is 500 ppm at a sintering temperature of 1400 degrees C.
Titulo: Effects of Fe2O3 doping on structural and electrical properties of 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The 8YSZ electrolyte doped with 500 ppm Fe2O3 shows 0.122 S cm(-1) and 0.598 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C in the ionic conductivity and maximum power density, respectively.
Titulo: Effects of Fe2O3 doping on structural and electrical properties of 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The power density of the cell based on the 8YSZ electrolyte doped with 500 ppm Fe2O3 is about 1.5 times higher than the cell using the pristine 8YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Effects of Fe2O3 doping on structural and electrical properties of 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thus, the introduction of a trace of Fe2O3 to the 8YSZ can improve its structural and electrical properties and finally SOFC performances.
Titulo: Effects of Fe2O3 doping on structural and electrical properties of 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells
